---
import placeholderImage from '../../../public/assets/5.webp';
import SideNavigation from './SideNavigation.astro';

const sections = [
  {
    id: 'client-background',
    title: 'Client Background',
    content: `my client is a researcher at a university in Canada, and he wants to use this project for both research purposes and as a source of income.
              He has the idea that we can improve remote workspaces using sounds and different techniques.
              He also has good connections in the research market, so he wants to use that to generate more income.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'client-requirements',
    title: 'Client Requirements',
    content: `To design a mobile app that uses sound to destress and increase the work quality and productivity of remote workers. It is to be used for research purposes, and to have the data sold later to research centers and universities.
              The project also has potential for future growth as a subscription-based model.
              The data will be collected with the knowledge of the users, and won't be used without their consent. Privacy considerations are key.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'problem-statement',
    title: 'Problem Statement',
    content: `I am a leader in my company, and I want to fix remote worker disconnection. I'm trying to align my team so they are in better sync, happier, and more productiveâ€”loving their job and their colleagues.
              However, remote workers are challenged to connect and openly share/engage to build true team synchronicity. 
              The recent challenges of remote work have only worsened social isolation and loneliness, which reduces creativity and increases turnover intention.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'business-goals',
    title: 'Business Goals',
    content: `
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400">
        <li>To have enough users for testing AI models, selling them, and offering analytics to research centers and universities.</li>
        <li>To keep the users engaged long-term.</li>
        <li>To make deals with large remote teams.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'project-goals',
    title: 'Project Goals',
    content: `To craft an intuitive UI that seamlessly addresses user needs, resolves pain points, and elevates the user experience. Our mission is to create a delightful journey that captivates users and inspires lasting engagement.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'hypotheses',
    title: 'Hypotheses',
    content: `
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400">
        <li class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400"> Remote workers often feel disconnected in their workplaces.</li>
        <li class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400"> Listening to music or sounds can help alleviate stress in remote workplaces.</li>
        <li class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400"> Listening to music increases worker productivity and work quality.</li>
        <li class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400"> Users are willing to use an app to listen to sounds that may seem strange (not music), but are proven to reduce stress and enhance productivity.</li>
        <li class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400"> The target audience includes tech-savvy youth aged 25-40 who work remotely.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
];
---


<main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
  <div class="lg:flex lg:gap-10">
    <!-- Side Navigation -->
    <aside class="lg:w-64 flex-shrink-0">
      <SideNavigation />
    </aside>

    <!-- Main Article -->
    <article class="mt-10 lg:mt-0 lg:flex-grow w-[80%] gap-10">
      <h1 class="text-6xl font-extrabold mb-8 text-primary-900 dark:text-white">Sanarte Case Study</h1>


      <!-- Dynamic Sections -->
      {
        sections.map((section) => (
          <section id={section.id} class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-900 dark:text-primary-200">{section.title}</h2>
            <p class="text-primary-400 dark:text-primary-400" set:html={section.content}></p>
          </section>
        ))
      }

      <!-- Table Section Example -->
      <section id="the-plan" class="mb-12 max-w-full ">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-900 dark:text-white">The plan</h2>
        <div class="max-w-full overflow-x-auto rounded-xl">
          <table class="max-w-full w-full bg-primary-800 rounded-xl divide-y divide-primary-600 dark:divide-primary-600">
            <thead class="bg-primary-800 dark:bg-primary-800 rounded-xl">
                      <tr>
                <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Method</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Type</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Related Hypotheses</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider">Why</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="bg-primary-900 divide-y-2 divide-primary-800 dark:bg-primary-900 dark:divide-primary-800 rounded-xl">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Competitor Analysis</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">N/A</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">To see what the competitors are doing, and what to learn from them</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Literature review (online search)</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Remote workers often feel disconnected in their workplaces</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">We are short on time on this project, and the client pays by day, so it will cost him a lot of time to have a survey of a big sample (also if these surveys are available from credible sources, and bigger sample why would I make my own survey)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Literature review (online search)</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">My target audience are youth from the age of 25-40 who work remotely, and are tech-savvy</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">We are short on time on this project, and the client pays by day, so it will cost him a lot of time to have a survey of a big sample (also if these surveys are available from credible sources, and bigger sample why would I make my own survey)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Literature review (research papers)</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Listening to music or sounds can help alleviate stress in remote workplaces.</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">This is a more credible source of information. Also, my client is a researcher, so they know how to work with me and support this step.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Literature review (research papers)</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Listening to music increases worker productivity and work quality.</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">This is a more credible source of information. Also, my client is a researcher, so they know how to work with me and support this step.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">User Interviews</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Exploratory</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4  text-sm text-primary-200">Users are willing to use an app to listen to sounds that may seem strange (not music), but are proven to reduce stress and enhance productivity.</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200">This is to verify with the users if this is scientifically proven to really help them, will they really use it, and what is the best channel to make it in.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
                  </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Image Sections -->
      <section id="user-persona" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-900 dark:text-white">User Persona</h2>
        <img src={placeholderImage} alt="User Persona" class="rounded-lg shadow-md" />
      </section>

      <section id="user-journey-map" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-900 dark:text-white">User Journey Map</h2>
        <img src={placeholderImage} alt="User Journey Map" class="rounded-lg shadow-md" />
      </section>

      <!-- Conclusion Section -->
      <section id="conclusion" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-primary-900 dark:text-white">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">
          The UX research revealed several key areas for improvement in our product. By addressing the identified pain points and implementing data-driven design decisions, we were able to significantly enhance user satisfaction and engagement metrics.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</main>
